The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International
                                                                                                                                                                                                       Since 1st March, 1999                                                               Pakistan hosted its leg of the Beijing Olympic torch relay today in an invitation-only event guarded by tight security imposed by the pro-China government.                 Thousands of Chinese expatriates are mobilising to defend the Olympic torch from pro-Tibet scum when it passes through the Australian capital.                   Revising his position on global warming, President George W. Bush proposed today a new target for stopping the growth of US greenhouse gas emissions by 2025.                   Vitamin supplements taken by millions of people in the hope of extending their lives may actually increase the risk of premature death in some cases, researchers said today.                             Pakistan Prime Minister Yousaf Raza Gilani with the Olympic torch in Islamabad on Wednesday. (AP)                                                                                                                                                                                    
